  ATMOSPHERE: (16785..16883) ";; < We fail this test because Hygiene is not enough to tell the two xs apart. Both _are_ the same"
  ATMOSPHERE: (16883..16904) "\n                    "
  ATMOSPHERE: (16904..17003) ";;   \"meaning\" of x (the free x in the root scope). Just the one in the template expansion of `foo`"
  ATMOSPHERE: (17003..17024) "\n                    "
  ATMOSPHERE: (17024..17120) ";;   is treated differently by syntax rules. We need to keep track of the provenance on a symbol"
  ATMOSPHERE: (17120..17141) "\n                    "
  ATMOSPHERE: (17141..17216) ";;   as well as the plain syntactic binding in order to tell the two apart."
